The paper discusses the implementation of isogeometric analysis in the open source package SfePy, which is a software for solving partial differential equations using the finite element method. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), which deals with numerical methods for solving mathematical problems, including partial differential equations. 

The paper also discusses the advantages of isogeometric analysis over the finite element method, which suggests that it could be relevant to the Computer Graphics (cs.CG) and Scientific Computing (cs.SC) categories. 

Additionally, the paper presents basic numerical examples, which could indicate that it is relevant to the Computational Engineering (cs.CE) and Modeling and Simulation (cs.MS) categories.
